Every night for 11 years...
Someone knocked on Margaret Hollis's door at exactly 3:17 AM.
She never opened it.
Margaret was 67 years old and lived alone in rural Vermont.
No neighbors within two miles.
No cameras.
No car in the driveway except her own.
The knocking started in 2009.
Always the same.
Three slow knocks.
A pause.
Then one more.
Every single night.
She called the police the first time in 2010.
They found nothing.
No footprints outside the door.
No tire tracks on the road.
Nothing disturbed in the snow.
Just... nothing.
She called again in 2013.
Same result.
By 2015 Margaret had stopped calling.
She simply... learned to live with it.
She told her daughter about it once.
Her daughter assumed she was imagining things.
Nobody took her seriously.
Until the night Margaret finally opened the door.
In 2020.
And what she found standing there...
Had been leaving her notes under the door for years.
Follow FileNotClosed for Part 2.
Because the notes...
Were written in her own handwriting.